      java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> toList()
      Note that this is a one-shot method, with the whole content of the iterator copied to the list. After calling this method, the iterator will be exhausted, and future invocations will return an empty list! (Too bad we can't differentiate between an empty iterator and an iterator that has already been iterated.)
